        <title>Activity: To calculate by using selected computations [LO 1.8]</title>
        <para id="id1170303579595">1. As with addition we can subtract more easily by rounding off numbers. In this way we estimate what the answer should be approximately! Work with a friend. Take turns to say the answers out loud to each other. Check the answers with a calculator. Feel free to ask your educator's help where needed.</para>
        <para id="id1170303167431">1.1 Subtract by rounding off both numbers to the nearest 10:</para>
        <para id="id1170300447963">a) 567 – 63</para>
        <para id="id1170302557600">b) 901 – 87</para>
        <para id="id1170303432296">c) 885 – 25</para>
        <para id="id3725736">d) 1 454 – 49</para>
        <para id="id1170302390417">e) 1 999 – 138</para>
        <para id="id2034703">1.2 Round both numbers to the nearest 100 and subtract:</para>
        <para id="id1170301570389">a) 973 – 214</para>
        <para id="id3777773">b) 1 259 – 993</para>
        <para id="id1170302968609">c) 6 048 – 3 512</para>
        <para id="id2229463">d) 9 999 – 8 234</para>
        <para id="id3954101">2. Let us look at different ways in which the difference between big numbers can be calculated!</para>
        <para id="id3771522">2.1 Can you still remember?</para>
        <para id="id1170302621200">Explain to friend how to round off to the nearest 1 000.</para>
