    <section id="id1170301684956">
      <title>Assessment</title>
      <para id="id1170303040127"><emphasis>Learning Outcome 1: </emphasis>The learner will be able to recognise, describe and represent numbers and their relationships, and to count, estimate, calculate and check with competence and confidence in solving problems.</para>
      <para id="id1170301829306"><emphasis>Assessment Standard 1.8:</emphasis> We know this when the learner estimates and calculates by selecting and using operations appropriate to solving problems;</para>
      <para id="id4003482">1.8.1 rounding off to the nearest 5, 10, 100 or 1 000;</para>
      <para id="id1170301566595">1.8.2 addition and subtraction of whole numbers with at least five digits.</para>
    </section>
